goals.rationale: A line chart can show the trend in yield over time, making it easy to identify any patterns or changes in yield over the two years of the dataset.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    
    plt.boxplot(data['yield'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation='vertical')
    
    median_yield = data['yield'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_yield, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Median Yield: {median_yield:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title("What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    avg_yield = data.groupby('variety')['yield'].mean()
    max_yield_variety = avg_yield.idxmax()
    max_yield = avg_yield.max()
    
    ax = avg_yield.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.axhline(y=max_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Yield: {max_yield:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Average Yield')
    plt.title('Which variety of barley has the highest yield on average?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='yield', by='site', grid=False)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("How does the yield of barley vary across different sites?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Site")
    plt.ylabel("Yield")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['yield'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Is there a trend in the yield of barley over time?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    heatmap_data = data.pivot_table(values='yield', index='site', columns='variety')
    sns.heatmap(heatmap_data, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.title("How does the yield of barley vary across different sites and varieties?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
